1) Install the Python Virtual Environment Package
yum install python3-virtualenv -y


2) Create the Virtual Environment - This will create a directory called new_virt_env, in which the venv exists
python -m venv new_virt_env


3) Activate the Virtual Environment
source new_virt_env/bin/activate
cd new_virt_env


4) Deactivate the Virtual Environment
Type "deactivate" while your inside your virtual environment


5) Remove the Virtual Environment by deleting the folder
rm -rf new_virt_env


6) Output currently installed packages via Freeze, and use the requirements.txt file to re-install the same ones if they've got deleted
pip freeze
pip freeze > requirements.txt
pip install -r requirements.txt

